article.description: Sophomore Morgan Johnson scored a career-high 22 points, Kachine Alexander added 21 points and 12 rebounds and No. 22 Iowa beat winless Northeastern 87-59 on Saturday.
article.headline: Iowa's rebounding helps keep Northeastern winless
article.linkText: No. 24 Iowa's rebounding comes up big in win
article.story:
IOWA CITY, Iowa -- Sophomore Morgan Johnson scored a career-high 22 points, Kachine Alexander added 21 points and 12 rebounds as Iowa (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) Iowa beat winless Northeastern 87-59 on Saturday.

Kelly Krei chipped in 18 points for the Hawkeyes (4-0), who overcame 19 turnovers by outrebounding the Huskies 51-27.

Northeastern (0-3) trailed 40-35 early in the second half. But Iowa went on a 9-2 run, capped by a Johnson jumper, to move ahead by 12.

The Hawkeyes used an 18-5 spurt to take an 80-55 lead with 2:49 left.

Kashaia Cannon had 16 points for the Huskies and Afreyea Tolbert added 12.
